  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with seasonal allergic conjunctivitis are normally advised to avoid contact lens
      wear when they are having symptoms. However, modern soft contact lenses which are disposed of
      daily offer the potential to protect and lubricate the ocular surface. This study examines
      this possible effect.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
